review.reviewBody:
Thida Thai has been my #1 go-to for years; no matter what neighborhood I live in, I order from here whenever possible. 
I ordered two of my usual favorites last night,  the 47. Pad See-Lew  and the 46. Pad Thai. I guess they got really busy after I ordered, because my estimated delivery time of less than 40 minutes turned into an hour and a half by the time it was actually delivered. Unfortunate, but these things happen. Once the food finally arrived, it wasn't as hot as usual, which was a little disappointing, and the chicken in the pad 47. Pad See-Lew was super dry and tough, and the portion a little small. If I'm going to wait over double the time to recieve the food, I'd hope it'd be super hot and fresh and full. 
Anyway, this definitely won't stop me from ordering from here again, as they are usually very consistent with quality (it's maybe just something for the owners to consider.) Aside from the above mentioned dishes, I highly recommend the massaman curry with coconut rice.
My fav 24. Panang Curry !!! So tasty, one of my go to spots in the west end! Fav Thai spot downtown :)

Panang curry was great, but the drunken prawns were overcooked and didn't have much flavour beyond the massive amount of bamboo shoots.
Skip the spring rolls entirely. Tiny and tasted like they were right out of the freezer.
They give small portion of the both items where I order large. And the taste is terrible. If they can't serve well in the last hour, they should not receive order.
I loved it all! Except the galanga in the #9 soup. Find it hard to eat and it ruins the soup. But I'll order here again.
